{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"R4 GROUNDING + BLOCKER (2026-07-18, investigation before rewrite/claim). Drove the \"rewrite plan -> pass gate -> implement -> land\" pipeline; STOPPED at a hard blocker and two grounding corrections. No ticket/description mutation, no claim, no code landed.\n\nBLOCKER (fatal to implement/land): R4's retrospective gate's primary anchor -- \">=8/10 of E2's class-4 (unnecessary-mechanism) mutants, <=1/10 controls\" -- is UNRUNNABLE because E2's mutant corpus DOES NOT EXIST. There is no docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e2_mutant_corpus.jsonl (verified: find, `git ls-files`, `git log --all`). E2 (d125, crude-volumed-scaup) is in_progress, not closed; its own description says the corpus + assemble_e2_mutants.py harness + baseline table are what it WILL produce. Epic 6982's 2026-07-16 comment confirms \"the E-experiments (E2/E3/E5/E6) + R-implementations (R1-R7) are unrun/unimplemented.\" `rebar ready` does NOT list R4 -- rebar treats it as blocked on depends_on d125. Per the epic rule \"no detection-bearing recommendation implemented without its eval gate,\" R4 must not land until E2 delivers class-4 mutants.\n\nGROUNDING CORRECTION 1 -- 5886 does NOT cleanly serve the NECESSITY probe (it serves the BUG TIER). 5886-d028-7954-4763 (unblacked-clownish-dunlin, bug) is a legit fix: unmapped inbound Jira status defaulted to \"open\", silently reopening closed tickets. Its plan HAS explicit Reproduction Steps + Expected/Actual, so it demonstrates necessity well -> the necessity probe would correctly NOT fire on it. The stub's \"its plan asserted a fix for behavior that already worked\" is unsupported: behavior was genuinely broken, and its reuse claim (\"fetcher.py already emits fetcher-unmapped-jira-status\") was TRUE -- that alert landed 2026-07-06 (git log -S, commit 9d5c9ba2d), 2 days before 5886's claim (2026-07-08). Epic E1 classifies the 3 misses (dc58/db7b/5886) as \"plan asserts a capability an existing module lacks\" = absent-capability (R1/class-1), NOT over-action (R4/class-4). => R4 needs a VALID class-4 positive fixture; 5886 is not one.\n\nGROUNDING CORRECTION 2 (confirms bug-tier premise) -- 5886's persisted plan review was an EXEMPT PASS: REVIEW_RESULT (git 44c01137c) = {\"runner\":\"exempt\",\"verdict\":\"PASS\",\"findings\":[],\"llm_calls\":0,\"coverage\":{\"exempt\":\"bug tickets are exempt from the plan-review gate\"}}. So \"today bugs skip substantive plan review\" is CONFIRMED. 5886 IS a good fixture for piece (b) the bug tier (a real bug that got only an exempt PASS), just not for piece (a) the necessity probe.\n\nSEAM GROUNDING (for when unblocked). Bug-tier claim-gate seam: workflow_ops.plan_review_precheck (workflow_ops.py:135-160) short-circuits ticket_type in (\"bug\",\"session_log\",\"code_review\",\"identity\") to orchestrator._exempt_verdict (orchestrator.py:676) -- no DET floor, no LLM. R4's bug tier runs DET floor + necessity probe here (advisory). Necessity probe: a new advisory criterion added to criteria_routing.json (entry shape: exec/facet/applies_at{scope,suppress_types,suppress_when}/block_threshold/default_posture/checklist[{key,check}]) with default_posture:\"advisory\" and, for the bug tier, NOT suppressing \"bug\" in suppress_types (contrast A1/E4/G7 which all suppress_types:[\"bug\"]); the id MUST also be registered in registry CANONICAL_LLM or registry.validate_packaged_routing() (registry.py:445) flags it ORPHAN and fails CI (per R2's grounding-correction comment on this epic). Pass-1 fan-out is pass1.run_pass1.\n\nRECOMMENDATION: (1) complete E2 (d125) to commit the class-4 mutant corpus + baseline; (2) select/construct a valid class-4 positive necessity fixture (5886 is not one -- reassign 5886 to the bug-tier fixture role); then (3) resume R4: claim -> implement advisory necessity criterion + bug tier -> validate >=8/10 class-4 discrimination on E2's corpus + bug-tier lifecycle test on 5886 -> land via Gerrit -> close. Alternatively, if R4 should not wait on E2, an operator decision is needed on whether R4 may generate its own deterministic class-4 fixtures (forking E2's centralized corpus) -- not taken unilaterally here."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784393245225099001,"uuid":"c98f84a9-1195-436a-bc2b-397716bac640"}